{
  "stem": "25598.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But I remember the field where there were a lot of people who had been deported before us, and they'd already been in this field for a number of days.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And you slept in the mud, and there was no food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And these-- as bad as we looked, those people looked a lot worse, because not only had they been brought there in trains the same as we were, but on top of that, they slept in the mud for several days.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And there, and there was no food, and they were cold.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And the clothes, and the shoes, everything was, was mud.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And, and they looked like bewildered people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And there were people from-- a lot of them were people from Bessarabia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And my mom and I visited my aunt in Bessarabia before, and, and the people were elegant.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And they wore hats, and they were-- and I couldn't understand what they're doing in this field.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was-- it was-- everything became unknown, from the way life used to be before when we knew exactly what every minute and every day will bring.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Suddenly, every minute was in a total unknown thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And not only did we not know what's going to be, but we knew that it's going to be bad.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whatever we didn't know, we knew it's going to be bad.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Eventually, after-- yeah, and eventually after a few days of, of us staying in this field too, they brought barges.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Dniester is a very big, fast, deep river.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had to cross the Dniester to get to the other side, to the Ukraine, where they were deporting a large segment of the population from Romania, particularly from Bukovina and Bessarabia.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my town was in the Province of Bukovina.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
